&lt;p&gt;Flex is hiring an Associate General Counsel, Product &amp;amp; Regulatory to join our Legal team. This role is an embedded legal and regulatory partner across Flex&#39;s Product, Engineering, Finance, and Business Development teams. You will counsel on product development and launches, navigate consumer financial regulation, and help shape how Flex builds compliantly at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise cross-functional stakeholders on new features, product enhancements, and go-to-market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regulatory change management; monitor the consumer financial landscape and translating developments into actionable guidance for the policy team and business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise senior leaders on consumer regulatory risk, enforcement trends, and litigation exposure across Flex’s product lines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Commercial team to review and negotiate business development and partnership agreements, providing regulatory and legal guidance on consumer finance terms and obligations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to legal technology initiatives, including tools and workflows that support the Product and Regulatory function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to building a modern, AI-native legal department developing workflows and tools that allow legal to move at the speed of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of legal experience in consumer financial services with exposure to fintech lending, bank-fintech partnership structures, state licensing, and federal and state consumer protection regulation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency across consumer financial regulation - CFPB rulemaking, TILA/Reg Z, UDAP/UDAAP, money transmission, and state licensing requirements for servicing and brokering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience as an embedded legal partner to product teams — comfortable advising on feature launches and speaking to regulatory risk at the leadership level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrives in a fast-moving environment — able to assess risk and provide sound guidance even when the full picture isn&#39;t yet clear.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, concise communicator who translates complex legal and regulatory concepts into plain language for business audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JD from an accredited law school; active bar admission required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with rent-adjacent fintech, payments, or embedded finance products&lt;/li&gt;
